An Ibadan chief, Oloye Adegboyega Adegoke has explained how Nigeria can overcome the present-day challenges. Some of the problems facing the country include insecurity, corruption, high inflation, economic instability, political warfare, and lack of patriotism among the citizens. Adegoke who is the Aare Onibon Balogun of Ibadan land has, however, advised the citizens to use all that they have to promote peace and unity among themselves. He said that the promotion of peace and unity will go long way for the country to overcome the present challenges. Adegoke in his Easter message to felicitate Christians also urged Nigerians to exercise faith and hope. He insisted that these are ways out of the present problems facing the country. Adegoke in his Easter message made available to DAILY POST in Ibadan, the Oyo State capital, also enjoined them to imbibe godly values of righteousness, peace and justice. Adegoke while speaking further, implored the people not to allow the lessons of Easter brought by the death and resurrection of Jesus Christ to elude them. He called on the citizens to prioritise love, peace and unity. He said These are the major instruments to tackle the current security and economic challenges bedevilling the country as we speak. Adegoke said, “On this year’s Easter, I call on all Christians and Nigerians to imbibe and sustain Godly values of righteousness, peace and justice which are the true nature of Christ. “As we celebrate, I urge all Christians and all Nigerians to work in love, peace and unity and exercise faith and hope, so we can overcome our current challenges and build a prosperous nation”.